\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Nominalist say that the models and systems that we use to understand the world (which includes but is not limited to the 'external' world) are, in a sense, arbitrary. And a model presents itself as useful because it allows us to make mostly successful predictions about the world around us, and our other knowledge and (to quote WVO Quine) web of beliefs can integrate these models without a whole lot of revision. So Nominalist aren't encumbered with the metaphysical problems that a belief in 'Truth' or 'Number' as real and existing entities creates.}{ }
